    "biochemistry": { n: 'Biochemistry studies cellular processes. Enzymes act as biological catalysts by lowering the activation energy required for metabolic reactions.', q: 'Which molecule is considered the primary energy currency of the living cell?', o: ['ATP (Adenosine Triphosphate)', 'DNA', 'RNA', 'Glucose'], a: 'ATP (Adenosine Triphosphate)' },
    "polymer": { n: 'Polymer chemistry investigates macromolecules. Step-growth and chain-growth are the primary mechanisms of polymerization.', q: 'Proteins are natural polymers made up of what monomer units?', o: ['Amino Acids', 'Nucleotides', 'Fatty Acids', 'Sugars'], a: 'Amino Acids' },
    "environmental": { n: 'Environmental chemistry analyzes chemical species in nature. Chlorofluorocarbons (CFCs) were responsible for ozone layer depletion.', q: 'Acid rain is primarily caused by atmospheric emissions of sulfur dioxide and:', o: ['Nitrogen Oxides', 'Carbon Monoxide', 'Methane', 'Ozone'], a: 'Nitrogen Oxides' },
